<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE41FF8AFF32FC355EAFFAE1" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE41FF8AFF32FC355846FBE1" blockId="1.[174,1232,1019,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">
Distribution. Palaearctic: From north Europe to souh Europe; North Africa, eastern 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFED8FBD55D1EFB82" box="[265,344,1051,1077]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Russia</collectingCountry>
. Oriental region. Middle East: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFD6EFBD55F6CFB82" box="[703,810,1051,1077]" name="Armenia" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFCE4FBD55FFAFB82" box="[821,956,1051,1077]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Tadjikistan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFC2BFBD558CBFB82" box="[1018,1165,1051,1077]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFB49FBD2588BFB81" box="[1176,1229,1052,1078]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFF7FFBF55D89FBE1" author="Rozkosny, R. &amp; Elberg, K." box="[174,463,1083,1110]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="167 - 193" refId="ref6845" refString="Rozkosny, R., Elberg, K. 1984. Family Sciomyzidae (Tetanoceridae). In: Soos, A. and Papp, L., eds. Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Vol. 9. Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, 167 - 193." type="book chapter" year="1984">Rozkošný, Elberg (1984)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFE0AFBF55FBAFBE1" author="Seddighi Sadr, F. &amp; Mohammadzade Namin, S." box="[475,1020,1083,1110]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="43 - 45" refId="ref6894" refString="Seddighi Sadr, F., Mohammadzade Namin, S. 2016. The snail killing flies (Diptera, Sciomyzidae) in Gilan Province, with a new record for Iranian fauna. Ukrainska Entomofaunistyka, 7 (1), 43 - 45." type="journal article" year="2016">Seddighi Sadr, Mohammadzade namin (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE41FF8AFF32FB955EAFFAE1" blockId="1.[174,1232,1019,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">
Biology. 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFEB0FB955E6CFBC1" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[353,554,1115,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="117 - 160" refId="ref6777" refString="Rozkosny, R. 1967. Zur Morphologie und Biologie der Metamorphosestadien mitteleuropaischer Sciomyziden (Diptera). Acta Academiae Scientiarum, Brno, 1 (4), 117 - 160." type="journal article" year="1967">Rozkošný (1967)</bibRefCitation>
described the larval morphology, and 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFC2CFB925896FBC1" author="Bratt, A. D. &amp; Knutson, L. V. &amp; Foote, B. A. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[1021,1232,1115,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref5863" refString="Bratt, A. D., Knutson, L. V., Foote, B. A., Berg, C. O. 1969. Biology of Pherbellia (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). New York Agricultural Experiment Station of Ithaca Memoirs, 404, 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1969">Bratt et al. (1969)</bibRefCitation>
described the life cycle and made the description of all immature stages. The larvae are predators of terrestrial and aquatic gastropods (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFD30FB555FEFFB01" author="Bratt, A. D. &amp; Knutson, L. V. &amp; Foote, B. A. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[737,937,1179,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref5863" refString="Bratt, A. D., Knutson, L. V., Foote, B. A., Berg, C. O. 1969. Biology of Pherbellia (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). New York Agricultural Experiment Station of Ithaca Memoirs, 404, 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1969">Bratt et al., 1969</bibRefCitation>
). Oviposition stimulus is a substrate moistened with fresh snail faeces or mucus of helicid-prey (
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFBD5FB755C96FB41" authority="Da" authorityName="Da" class="Gastropoda" family="Geomitridae" genus="Cernuella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="virgata">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE41FF8AFBD5FB755896FB62" box="[1028,1232,1211,1237]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Cernuella virgata</emphasis>
Da
</taxonomicName>
Costa) (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFEEBFB155E44FB41" author="Coupland, J. B." box="[314,514,1243,1270]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="183 - 189" refId="ref6020" refString="Coupland, J. B. 1996. Influence of snail faeces and mucus on oviposition and larval behaviour of Pherbellia cinerella (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Journal of Chemical Ecology, 22, 183 - 189." type="journal article" year="1996">Coupland, 1996</bibRefCitation>
). The puparium is formed outside the shell prey, and in southern 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFEF1FB325D36FAA1" box="[288,368,1276,1302]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">France</collectingCountry>
adults are overwintering (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFD7AFB355F6AFAA1" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[683,812,1275,1302]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref7413" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1989. Dipteres Sciomyzidae Euro-mediterraneens. Faune de France. France et Regions limitrophes. N ° 72. Federation Francaise de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles, Paris. 1 - 300." type="book chapter" year="1989">Vala, 1989</bibRefCitation>
) but in 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFC5FFB355F9CFAA2" box="[910,986,1275,1301]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Russia</collectingCountry>
has been found that pupa are overwintering also (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFDD5FAD55EF8FA81" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[516,702,1307,1334]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). This species has a short developmental time and is multivoltine (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFE4BFAF55E5CFAE2" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[410,538,1339,1365]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref7413" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1989. Dipteres Sciomyzidae Euro-mediterraneens. Faune de France. France et Regions limitrophes. N ° 72. Federation Francaise de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles, Paris. 1 - 300." type="book chapter" year="1989">Vala, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFDF4FAF55E9BFAE1" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[549,733,1339,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
